text: Cyclone Hudhud was a very severe cyclonic storm. The storm originated in the northern Indian Ocean. The cyclone killed over 100 people across India. Its winds were near 130 mph. It struck in October 2014. The cyclone caused $11 billion (USD) in damage. Category:Cyclonic storms Category:2014 in weather Category:October 2014 events Category:2014 in India
title: Cyclone Hudhud
